1
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:34,920
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:37,690
[Episode 11]

3
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:43,420
[Tiecheng Juvenile Correctional Facility]

4
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:39,979
Listen carefully.

5
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,710
Only immediate family and guardians are

6
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:42,640
allowed to visit.

7
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,509
Please go back.

8
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:45,509
Wait, what about the snowman and this...

9
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:46,410
Can we give him the snacks?

10
00:01:46,410 --> 00:01:48,000
These items are not allowed
to be brought inside.

11
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:48,860
Please go back.

12
00:01:53,039 --> 00:01:54,300
Are you satisfied now?

13
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,560
He made it very clear.

14
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:59,509
Only immediate family and guardians
can go visit him.

15
00:01:59,509 --> 00:02:00,710
You guys can't get in.

16
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,510
Is there any other way?

17
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:04,120
Maybe I can file an application?

18
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,650
I'll come back in a few days.

19
00:02:05,810 --> 00:02:07,270
Applications won't help.

20
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:09,210
I already asked around for you.

21
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:11,270
Only Mr. Ding can go in here.

22
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:13,490
So, Dad.

23
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:14,910
You knew all along

24
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:16,910
that we couldn't see Xiaoman today?

25
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:17,590
Well.

26
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:19,000
It's not...

27
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:20,750
It's not about when I knew.

28
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:22,280
It's about their rules.

29
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:24,950
I'll figure it out myself.

30
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,079
That temper.

31
00:02:26,590 --> 00:02:27,990
Who did she get that from?

32
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:30,840
What are you waiting for? Let's go.

33
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:35,670
We brought the snowman for nothing.
It's all melted.

34
00:02:35,670 --> 00:02:36,630
Forget about the snowman.

35
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:39,090
You two should eat it yourselves
to cool off.

36
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,910
Xiaodan.

37
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:50,030
Hear me out.

38
00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:52,490
I didn't tell you before,

39
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:55,079
and you should understand why.

40
00:02:55,079 --> 00:02:57,750
I was afraid it would affect
your college entrance examination.

41
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,680
Yes, Sweetie.

42
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,840
Don't be mad.

43
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:01,990
Your dad did it for your own good.

44
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:04,150
He was afraid you'd regret it later.

45
00:03:04,430 --> 00:03:05,680
Open the door, Sweetie.

46
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,140
Come and open the door now.

47
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,940
You two are making me regret it right now.

48
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,150
I regret not spending enough time

49
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,280
with Xiaoman over the past few months.

50
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:14,470
I listened to you, didn't I?

51
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:15,520
I focused on my studies

52
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,250
and studied hard.

53
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:17,720
I did everything I should.

54
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:20,750
I went to Beijing
for the hosting competition.

55
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,270
I suffered a fiasco.

56
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,310
But I don't regret it.

57
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,079
I feel like I tried my best.

58
00:03:26,079 --> 00:03:27,630
I tried. I did it.

59
00:03:27,970 --> 00:03:30,570
But if I let others
change the course of my life,

60
00:03:30,630 --> 00:03:32,100
that's when I'd regret it.

61
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,200
Sweetie, please stop it.

62
00:03:37,310 --> 00:03:39,910
All right, old man. Don't be mad.

63
00:03:40,870 --> 00:03:43,000
She's still young. She's just a child.

64
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:43,840
Okay?

65
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:44,800
Young?

66
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,910
She's all grown up now.

67
00:04:17,420 --> 00:04:21,670
[One month later]

68
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:25,390
Why isn't Xiaodan back yet?

69
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:26,970
Yeah.

70
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,240
I'm worried sick.

71
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:29,360
Look at the time.

72
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:32,159
Welcome back, Sweetie.

73
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:35,830
Did you ask the school office?

74
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:37,510
Xia Lei's admission letter

75
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:38,600
arrived 2 days ago.

76
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,360
Why hasn't yours arrived yet?

77
00:04:41,330 --> 00:04:43,170
Could it be that Tongzhou University

78
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:46,170
has raised
its cutoff score significantly this year?

79
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,310
Stop speculating there.

80
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:51,520
I'm also starting to get worried.

81
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:52,380
How about this?

82
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,070
I'll call the admissions office

83
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:56,270
of Tongzhou University.

84
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:56,830
Yeah.

85
00:04:57,159 --> 00:04:58,400
Call them now. Hurry.

86
00:04:58,430 --> 00:05:00,490
Their number is
in the admissions brochure.

87
00:05:00,490 --> 00:05:01,120
-Come on.
-Where is it?

88
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:01,800
Here it is.

89
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:03,170
Let's look for it.

90
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,510
Here. Is this it?

91
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:06,680
No. Not this one.

92
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,870
It's a big one.

93
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,510
-A big one.
-It should be down there.

94
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:11,170
-Not this one.
-It's not here.

95
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:12,260
It's always been at the bottom.

96
00:05:12,260 --> 00:05:13,390
Where did you put it?

97
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:18,290
-I can't find it.
-Alright, stop looking for it.

98
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:23,040
What's this?

99
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:25,310
What is this?

100
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:33,110
An admission letter
from Tongzhou University!

101
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,480
You got in! You got in, Sweetie!

102
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:38,970
Come on, let me take a look!

103
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:41,270
My baby!

104
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:42,480
Sweetie!

105
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,480
Sweetie, I'm so happy!

106
00:05:44,850 --> 00:05:47,280
Good girl.
I knew my daughter was the best.

107
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,510
I told you

108
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,920
I'd get in, right?

109
00:05:51,130 --> 00:05:52,870
You didn't believe me and got mad at me.

110
00:05:52,870 --> 00:05:54,360
It was all my fault before.

111
00:05:54,630 --> 00:05:56,570
You were right. So right.

112
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,400
You're always right, daughter.

113
00:05:58,510 --> 00:05:59,120
Yan,

114
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,830
let's go out and celebrate, okay?

115
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:02,830
No problem! What do you two want to eat?

116
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:03,870
It's on me today.

117
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:06,480
Xiaodan loves
sweet and sour pork ribs the most!

118
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:08,680
-Okay, no problem.
-I... I'm going out for a bit.

119
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,210
Why are you going out again?

120
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,120
Don't go. Come back here.

121
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:14,100
Don't you get it?

122
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,050
She can go wherever she wants

123
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:17,540
and do whatever she wants now.

124
00:06:17,540 --> 00:06:18,980
Come on, you old man.

125
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,200
-Come on.
-Let me see.

126
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,450
Do you think Xiaoman can hear it?

127
00:06:25,450 --> 00:06:27,850
Play it here,
and he'll definitely hear it.

128
00:06:43,290 --> 00:06:46,680
[Tiecheng Juvenile Correctional Facility]

129
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,400
Any movement?

130
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,880
I can't see anything.

131
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:57,750
♪ A pair of hands
that can no longer be beautified ♪

132
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:00,590
♪ Yet envelops with warmth ♪

133
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,530
Xiaoman.

134
00:06:59,870 --> 00:07:00,510
Xiaoman.

135
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:02,000
What are you doing?

136
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:03,100
♪ The constant nagging and care ♪

137
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,670
♪ So guilty that I didn't cherish it ♪

138
00:07:07,190 --> 00:07:10,110
♪ She didn't approve of me
being immersed in the music scene ♪

139
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:09,080
Let me see.

140
00:07:09,310 --> 00:07:09,970
Here you go.

141
00:07:10,470 --> 00:07:12,850
♪ But a mother's love never wanes ♪

142
00:07:13,490 --> 00:07:15,610
♪ Determined to break free from
the struggle within myself ♪

143
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:18,390
♪ To finally repay
your love and kindness ♪

144
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,270
It should work.

145
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:20,510
There should be a gap at the bottom.

146
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:22,570
♪ As the warm spring gives way to rain,
your love warms my heart ♪

147
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:21,630
No, actually.

148
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:26,570
♪ All my life you looked after me
without words ♪

149
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:23,600
What are you doing?

150
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,240
What are you doing?

151
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,240
Did you guys do that?

152
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:25,720
What are you doing?

153
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,580
Turn it off now!

154
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:27,720
Take it away!

155
00:07:27,370 --> 00:07:30,580
♪ It is your warm gaze ♪

156
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:28,870
Don't you know where you are?

157
00:07:28,870 --> 00:07:30,240
Take that down! Put it away!

158
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,480
Take it away now! Turn it off!

159
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,790
♪ That teaches me to persevere... ♪

160
00:07:32,830 --> 00:07:33,600
Unbelievable!

161
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,120
-Take it down.
-How could you play it here?

162
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,920
Take it down. Look where you are.

163
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,460
You are students, aren't you?

164
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:42,590
Just finished your college entrance exam?

165
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:45,070
Listen, kids.

166
00:07:45,510 --> 00:07:46,270
If you want to visit someone,

167
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:47,870
we have to go through proper procedures.

168
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:49,480
Making a ruckus as you did is

169
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:51,000
against the rules.

170
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,120
Sirs, we have a friend in there.

171
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:53,680
W-We just wanted...

172
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,420
I know you have a friend in there.

173
00:07:55,420 --> 00:07:57,120
Were it not for a friend,
who would come all this way here?

174
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,080
Well, then... Sirs...

175
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,680
Please, just 2 minutes.

176
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:01,270
Could you please let us see him
for just 2 minutes?

177
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,240
No way.

178
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,120
If everyone who comes here can get in,

179
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,720
tell me, is this
a juvenile detention center

180
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,050
or a class reunion site?

181
00:08:07,610 --> 00:08:08,830
Sirs, please.

182
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,640
Just let me finish playing this song.

183
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:11,600
If my friend hears it,

184
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,260
he'll surely know we're here.

185
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,390
Please... Please...

186
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,040
No can do.

187
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,680
I understand your feelings,

188
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,510
but rules are rules.

189
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:19,430
Look.

190
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:21,270
The area
near the juvenile detention center is

191
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:22,870
a strictly controlled zone.

192
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,190
If you make loud noises in this area,

193
00:08:25,450 --> 00:08:26,640
at best, you'll be driven away;

194
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,170
at worst,
you'll face serious consequences.

195
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,320
Well... Um...

196
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:33,030
Sirs...

197
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:33,510
Just leave.

198
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:35,270
Did they hear it clearly inside?

199
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:36,120
Go back now.

200
00:08:36,270 --> 00:08:37,200
Hurry and leave.

201
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,030
-Take care.
-Be careful.

202
00:08:48,010 --> 00:08:49,070
They're just kids.

203
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:53,750
Tie that tape recorder tight.

204
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,080
Take it slow on your way.

205
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,080
Yes, sirs.

206
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:58,510
-Press... Turn it on.
-Sirs, goodbye.

207
00:08:58,510 --> 00:08:58,870
Ride slowly.

208
00:08:58,870 --> 00:08:59,730
Sirs, goodbye.

209
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:00,600
Turn it on.

210
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:03,370
♪ It is your warm gaze ♪

211
00:09:00,870 --> 00:09:01,470
Turn it on.

212
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:02,870
-Hurry, let's go.
-It's on again!

213
00:09:02,870 --> 00:09:04,110
Are you two putting on a show?

214
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:06,640
♪ That teaches me to persevere
and focus on the road ahead ♪

215
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:05,670
Let's go, let's go.

216
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,840
Playing such a little trick.

217
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:11,580
♪ Reminding me not to give up
even when I fall ♪

218
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:09,000
Take it slow on the road.

219
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,810
Go back home.

220
00:09:18,790 --> 00:09:20,320
Let's go play it in the back.

221
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:21,760
Put it here, here.

222
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:22,870
Let's put it in the middle.

223
00:09:22,870 --> 00:09:23,510
Yeah.

224
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,400
No, make it face this way.

225
00:09:44,890 --> 00:09:48,410
♪ A pair of hands
that can no longer be beautified ♪

226
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:51,440
♪ Yet envelops with warmth ♪

227
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,600
♪ The constant nagging and care ♪

228
00:09:53,620 --> 00:09:56,080
♪ So guilty that I didn't cherish it ♪

229
00:09:57,670 --> 00:10:00,470
♪ As the warm spring gives way to rain,
your love warms my heart ♪

230
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:04,870
♪ All my life you looked after me
without words ♪

231
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:08,410
♪ It is your warm gaze ♪

232
00:10:08,890 --> 00:10:11,590
♪ Reminding me not to give up
even when I fall ♪

233
00:10:12,010 --> 00:10:16,850
♪ That teaches me to persevere
and focus on the road ahead ♪

234
00:10:17,850 --> 00:10:20,820
♪ There's no way to explain
how repay your love ♪

235
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,040
♪ Your love is vast and infinite ♪

236
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:29,270
♪ Please allow me to say
I really love you ♪

237
00:10:42,740 --> 00:10:44,080
Xiaodan, you've got to try this.

238
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,240
My husband cooked these pig trotters
especially for you.

239
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,080
Okay. Thank you, Mrs. Tong.

240
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,670
Let me try.

241
00:10:47,670 --> 00:10:49,480
Eat a trotter,
and you'll grab success in Shanghai.

242
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,210
-Here.
-Yes.

243
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:50,870
Grab success.

244
00:10:50,870 --> 00:10:51,410
Lei.

245
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,930
It's so good. Mr. Xia is a great cook.

246
00:10:52,930 --> 00:10:53,440
Hurry.

247
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,140
Come on.

248
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:54,970
Let me serve you some.

249
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:55,720
Thank you, madam.

250
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:56,650
Look at Xiaodan.

251
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,080
We watched her grow up.

252
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:58,910
Now that she's leaving,

253
00:10:58,910 --> 00:11:00,970
I don't know when we'll see her again.

254
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:02,270
What are you saying?

255
00:11:02,510 --> 00:11:04,640
Isn't your Lei going to Shanghai, too?

256
00:11:04,930 --> 00:11:05,440
They will

257
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,630
keep in touch anyway.

258
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:07,240
Yes, yes.

259
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,320
Just knowing

260
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:12,270
we have old friends like you in Shanghai

261
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:13,670
makes us feel much more at ease.

262
00:11:13,670 --> 00:11:14,150
Yes.

263
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:15,110
You know,

264
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,040
well, all these years,

265
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:19,440
we've been preparing for this day.

266
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:20,770
But now that it's come,

267
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:24,270
I feel so empty inside.

268
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:25,730
-I'm a bit sad to let go.
-He's feeling melancholy.

269
00:11:25,730 --> 00:11:27,910
Come on. You have to let go,
even if you're reluctant to,

270
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:28,720
as a parent.

271
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:29,270
Yes, yes.

272
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:30,030
What do we want?

273
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:31,120
It's all for the children.

274
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,000
-Exactly.
-Yeah.

275
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,440
Excellent! In the future,

276
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,270
you two should study hard, right?

277
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:36,320
Get into a good workplace

278
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,960
-No...
-and have a bright future.

279
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,270
They'll be great entrepreneurs!

280
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:40,080
Right?

281
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:43,480
Isn't that what you think, too?

282
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:43,910
Yes.

283
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:45,890
I've been looking forward to this day.

284
00:11:45,890 --> 00:11:47,050
You may not know.

285
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,030
A couple of days ago,

286
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:48,870
his plant held

287
00:11:48,870 --> 00:11:51,320
a farewell party for Yan.

288
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:53,390
Everything was fine at first,

289
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:56,030
but Zhuang Dalin
insisted on calling Yan a deserter

290
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:57,080
and talking nonsense.

291
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,440
I didn't even want to listen.

292
00:11:58,440 --> 00:12:00,840
Later, Yan didn't say a word
in his defense.

293
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,240
Once the transfer order came,

294
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,080
he walked around the plant

295
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,320
for a whole day

296
00:12:05,140 --> 00:12:06,720
without even coming back for dinner.
(Shanghai dialect)

297
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:07,320
What?

298
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:08,680
What do you mean?

299
00:12:08,940 --> 00:12:10,670
He didn't come back for dinner.

300
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:11,210
Geez.

301
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,120
It's okay.

302
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,440
How disheartening.

303
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,720
Yeah.

304
00:12:17,050 --> 00:12:19,340
We've been here for most of our lives.

305
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:21,320
How could we not have feelings
for this place?

306
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:21,780
Indeed.

307
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,360
Why are we going through

308
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,270
the trouble of moving back

309
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,480
at our age?

310
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:27,240
It's for our daughter.

311
00:12:27,270 --> 00:12:28,550
For the kid.

312
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,440
You should just ignore... ignore them.

313
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:31,870
Right.

314
00:12:32,030 --> 00:12:33,510
Chief Engineer Yan
has put his heart and soul

315
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:35,720
into the plant all these years.

316
00:12:36,270 --> 00:12:38,270
-Everyone knows that.
-We all know.

317
00:12:38,270 --> 00:12:38,790
Exactly.

318
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:41,480
It's understandable
that you're planning for your child.

319
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,010
Isn't it?

320
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,580
Let's forget about it.

321
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:45,150
Lei,

322
00:12:45,580 --> 00:12:48,380
you're going to Shanghai soon, right?

323
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:50,590
My wife and I will be in Shanghai.

324
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:51,510
We'll be there.

325
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:54,360
Well, just see our home as your home.

326
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,640
Come over whenever you're free.

327
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,510
My wife will cook whatever you want.

328
00:12:58,510 --> 00:12:59,020
Do you hear me?

329
00:12:59,020 --> 00:12:59,450
Okay.

330
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,870
I'd like to thank you, Chief Engineer Yan,
on behalf of Xia Lei.

331
00:13:02,870 --> 00:13:03,360
Cheers, Mr. Yan.

332
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:03,720
Cheers.

333
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:04,780
Let's have a drink.

334
00:13:05,030 --> 00:13:06,160
Chief Engineer Yan.

335
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,460
Shanghai is your home,

336
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,910
but East Chemical Plant is also your home.

337
00:13:08,910 --> 00:13:09,390
Yes.

338
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,840
Come back whenever you miss us.

339
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,380
I will always have

340
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:15,640
a hearty family meal

341
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:16,720
ready for you.

342
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:19,120
Come on, let's drink together.

343
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:19,840
Together!

344
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:20,910
You two...

345
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:22,440
-Good luck at school.
-Today's kids are so nice.

346
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:22,960
Really.

347
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,680
Wish you all the best.

348
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:27,040
Xiaoman,

349
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:30,030
while writing this letter to you,

350
00:13:30,910 --> 00:13:32,370
I couldn't help wondering

351
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:34,630
what you are doing right now.

352
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:36,870
The other day,

353
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:39,800
Xia Lei and I
tried every possible means to visit you,

354
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:41,120
but we failed.

355
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,300
Looking at the high walls,

356
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,200
I felt so sad thinking

357
00:13:45,910 --> 00:13:47,550
that you were trapped inside

358
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:49,440
because of me.

359
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,910
On August 20th,

360
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,910
Xia Lei and I played "Really Love You"

361
00:13:53,910 --> 00:13:56,120
outside the walls.

362
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:58,440
I wonder if you heard it.

363
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:01,040
When the song played,

364
00:14:01,910 --> 00:14:03,270
I remembered how you looked

365
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:04,800
singing this song on stage.

366
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:07,200
You were so dazzling and handsome.

367
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:10,320
It also brought back
many amazing memories.

368
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,960
Six months will go by quickly.

369
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,400
Take good care of yourself in there.

370
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,000
Hope when I see you again,

371
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:23,840
you'll still be that shining,
high-spirited Zhang Xiaoman.

372
00:14:25,870 --> 00:14:27,630
I'm leaving our plant today

373
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:29,560
for the school in Shanghai.

374
00:14:30,210 --> 00:14:31,660
I got
into the Architectural Design program

375
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:33,060
at Tongzhou University.

376
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:36,440
The thought of unfamiliar university life

377
00:14:36,630 --> 00:14:38,560
makes me both curious and nervous.

378
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,920
But I know that wherever my ship sails,

379
00:14:42,210 --> 00:14:43,940
my first mate will never leave,

380
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:47,200
so I am full of courage
for the unknown ahead.

381
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:48,600
Xiaoman,

382
00:14:49,370 --> 00:14:51,620
I look forward to seeing you again

383
00:14:52,370 --> 00:14:54,370
and exploring our future together.

384
00:14:55,630 --> 00:14:59,720
We share the cold waves, the wind,
the thunder, and the lightning.

385
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:04,550
We share the mist,
the drifting clouds, and the rainbow.

386
00:15:06,190 --> 00:15:07,920
We could be temporarily apart,

387
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:11,360
yet bound together for life.

388
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,040
From Xiaodan.

389
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:26,530
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

390
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,220
Do you like this color?

391
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:33,580
I'm just a college student.
What do I need a suit for?

392
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:35,360
On TV,

393
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,840
those college students
in debate competitions and such

394
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,270
all wear suits and ties.

395
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:41,020
-Exactly.
-If there's a formal occasion later,

396
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,420
you can't go without one.

397
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:43,320
You need a suit.

398
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:43,810
Try it on.

399
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:44,610
Try it.

400
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:52,720
It fits well.

401
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:53,870
-Look!
-Nice!

402
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:54,670
-Good.
-Right?

403
00:15:54,670 --> 00:15:55,510
-That's good!
-Pretty good.

404
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,640
Put the collar down.

405
00:15:57,270 --> 00:15:58,470
Put down your collar.

406
00:15:58,910 --> 00:15:59,270
Let me see.

407
00:15:59,270 --> 00:16:00,400
Put the collar down.

408
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:02,240
Don't I look handsome this way?

409
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:04,440
No wonder they say clothes make the man.

410
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,730
Son, come over here.

411
00:16:06,910 --> 00:16:07,630
Not bad.

412
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,260
-Not bad, huh?
-Handsome.

413
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:11,150
Take it.

414
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,080
Be frugal at home
but generous when traveling.

415
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:15,080
It's for your tuition and living expenses.

416
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,340
Don't be stingy when you get to Shanghai.

417
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,660
Spend when you need to.

418
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:21,080
Treat your classmates
to meals or whatever.

419
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:23,270
Your dad and I aren't good with people,

420
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:24,360
so we've suffered.

421
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,910
Don't let it bite you, too.

422
00:16:26,310 --> 00:16:28,000
Mom, this is too much money.

423
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:28,480
I...

424
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,330
I'll use this 600 yuan first.

425
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,030
If it's not enough, I'll ask for more.

426
00:16:35,030 --> 00:16:36,120
-Boy...
-What are you doing?

427
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,390
We want you to take it, so just accept it.

428
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:38,020
Do as your mom said.

429
00:16:38,020 --> 00:16:39,750
Money can put your mind at ease.

430
00:16:40,030 --> 00:16:41,230
Just take it. Come on.

431
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:43,120
Dad, you keep this for now.

432
00:16:43,590 --> 00:16:44,110
Well...

433
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:47,610
This money is meant
for the man in this suit.

434
00:17:00,150 --> 00:17:06,069
♪ So many mountains I've climbed, rivers
I've crossed, trial after trial ♪

435
00:17:06,099 --> 00:17:11,319
♪ So many cliffs I've scaled, risky roads
I've walked, bend after bend ♪

436
00:17:09,859 --> 00:17:10,990
Where are you going?

437
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:18,160
♪ Through disasters I've caused,
hardships and hunger I've suffered ♪

438
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:12,859
Oh, I missed it.

439
00:17:13,150 --> 00:17:13,630
Water.

440
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,569
Dad, the view outside is amazing.

441
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:18,190
It's full of mountains.

442
00:17:18,190 --> 00:17:22,430
♪ The heart of the people
crossing the bridge rages like wildfire ♪

443
00:17:20,109 --> 00:17:20,920
Boy,

444
00:17:21,589 --> 00:17:22,310
you're a college student now.

445
00:17:22,310 --> 00:17:23,920
How can you not know such common sense?

446
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:25,790
Aren't we j-just living in a hilly area?

447
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:29,840
♪ I've walked through dark alleys, hit
against high walls, fallen into the pond ♪

448
00:17:26,579 --> 00:17:28,270
Isn't our plant located in the mountains?

449
00:17:28,270 --> 00:17:29,920
You're also sending your child
to college, right?

450
00:17:29,870 --> 00:17:36,400
♪ I've pursued my ideals, hated this body,
and been to the middle of nowhere ♪

451
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:33,250
He got into Shanghai Huigong University.

452
00:17:33,420 --> 00:17:35,220
Wow, that's a great university!

453
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:36,590
Not just in Shanghai.

454
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:41,660
♪ Gazing at the moon in a foreign land
in the gap of the city ♪

455
00:17:36,610 --> 00:17:37,980
It's one of the best in the whole country.

456
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:38,310
Yeah.

457
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,680
You must be tired.
Come on, sit down for a while.

458
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,960
-No, you sit.
-Sit.

459
00:17:41,820 --> 00:17:46,070
♪ Wishing only for the credit of one
who has crossed the bridge ♪

460
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,830
He's young.
Let him stand for a bit. It's fine.

461
00:17:43,830 --> 00:17:45,000
He's going to get water. Sit down, boy.

462
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:45,590
Sit down.

463
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:46,540
Thank you, sir.

464
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:47,610
-I'll go get some water.
-Thanks.

465
00:17:47,610 --> 00:17:48,090
No worries.

466
00:17:47,990 --> 00:17:50,640
♪ Look at the river flowing ♪

467
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:54,050
♪ Where will the young man
on the bridge go? ♪

468
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:54,790
Hold on a bit.

469
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:56,870
♪ The vibrant spring sees flying birds
and thriving greenery ♪

470
00:17:55,020 --> 00:17:56,500
He just dotes on his child.

471
00:17:56,890 --> 00:17:59,430
♪ But my heart remains the same ♪

472
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:58,070
It's out.

473
00:17:59,310 --> 00:18:00,310
We can see the sunshine.

474
00:17:59,970 --> 00:18:03,860
♪ Listen to the wuthering wind
in the fog ♪

475
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:03,110
To quote your mother,

476
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:06,510
it's like studying hard for over a decade

477
00:18:03,890 --> 00:18:06,120
♪ The one crossing the bridge
has no fear of the road ahead ♪

478
00:18:06,140 --> 00:18:07,450
♪ With the figure fading away ♪

479
00:18:06,590 --> 00:18:08,640
and finally coming out of the cave.

480
00:18:07,540 --> 00:18:09,960
♪ The reckless youth is gone from now on ♪

481
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,210
We've entered the pass?

482
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:11,750
Right. We've entered it.

483
00:19:01,850 --> 00:19:02,480
Son.

484
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:04,000
Son.

485
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,640
It's uncomfortable sleeping here, huh?

486
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,370
Dad, you sit.

487
00:19:09,430 --> 00:19:10,500
No, no, no.

488
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,100
I got you a sleeping berth.

489
00:19:12,790 --> 00:19:13,310
What?

490
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:14,310
A sleeping berth?

491
00:19:14,310 --> 00:19:15,110
A bottom bunk.

492
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:16,550
A bottom bunk?

493
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:19,160
The bunk down below.

494
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,130
Under the seats.

495
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,010
Crawl in from... from here.

496
00:19:23,590 --> 00:19:24,520
Crawl from here.

497
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:25,840
Right.

498
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:27,880
Be careful.

499
00:19:29,070 --> 00:19:30,880
I lay like this when I was young.

500
00:19:32,470 --> 00:19:33,310
It's fine.

501
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:36,540
Here.

502
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:39,520
Be careful. Watch your head.

503
00:19:41,510 --> 00:19:41,960
Good.

504
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:43,730
Use this bag as a pillow.

505
00:19:44,310 --> 00:19:44,920
Here.

506
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:46,960
Come on.

507
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:48,440
Give me your glasses.

508
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:49,700
I'll keep them for you.

509
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,190
[Shanghai Huigong University]

510
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:55,680
666. Here it is.

511
00:19:56,630 --> 00:19:57,890
That's a lucky number.

512
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:01,900
Hello, sir.

513
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:02,680
Hello, young man.

514
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:03,160
Hello.

515
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:03,620
Hello.

516
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:04,680
Here. This is your bed.

517
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:05,200
Okay.

518
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,550
My name is Wang Defu.

519
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:07,750
You can call me Eight.

520
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:09,480
Nice to meet you.

521
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:10,400
I'm Xia Lei.

522
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,060
Hi, Xia Lei.

523
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:12,350
"Eight"?

524
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:12,750
Yes.

525
00:20:12,780 --> 00:20:14,430
Do you have 7 siblings?

526
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:16,180
No, it's because I have a huge appetite.

527
00:20:16,180 --> 00:20:17,450
I can eat 8 taels of rice per meal,

528
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:18,780
so my nickname is Eight.

529
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,680
Eight taels of rice? That's impressive.

530
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:22,310
You don't eat other dishes?

531
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,730
I'll put the cup up here for you.

532
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:27,240
[Souvenir of 1996 anniversary celebration,
East Integrated Chemical Plant]

533
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:27,180
Let me do it. I'll handle it.

534
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,590
Sir, are you from the Third Front Plant?

535
00:20:29,590 --> 00:20:31,650
You know about the Third Front Plant?

536
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:32,830
I'm from one, too.

537
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,240
I'm a Third Front Plant kid,

538
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:35,070
from Xianyang, Shaanxi.

539
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:37,000
Xianyang 701. Have you heard of it?

540
00:20:37,830 --> 00:20:38,830
I-I know your plant.

541
00:20:38,830 --> 00:20:40,200
Yours is in Liaoning, right?

542
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,830
-Yes.
-The one who makes smoke-free gunpowder.

543
00:20:41,830 --> 00:20:42,400
Exactly.

544
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,730
But judging by your accent,

545
00:20:44,730 --> 00:20:46,680
you don't sound like you're from Shaanxi.

546
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:49,240
I grew up
traveling all over with my parents.

547
00:20:49,260 --> 00:20:50,830
And we finally settled in Shaanxi.

548
00:20:50,830 --> 00:20:53,440
We Third Front Plant folks
don't really have an accent.

549
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:54,680
You don't have a Liaoning accent, either.

550
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:56,810
True. We also have a mix of people there

551
00:20:56,810 --> 00:20:58,190
from all over the country.

552
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,240
Stop it now.

553
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:01,480
You have to catch a train this afternoon.

554
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,000
Oh, yes.

555
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:02,680
Let me check the time.

556
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:03,540
What time is it?

557
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:05,790
Fine. Make the bed yourself.

558
00:21:11,030 --> 00:21:12,960
Alright, you may go back upstairs.

559
00:21:16,070 --> 00:21:17,130
What are you doing?

560
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,480
Go back.

561
00:21:19,410 --> 00:21:20,630
Are you coming back with me?

562
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:21,740
I'll see you off.

563
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:24,200
Remember to eat well.

564
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:27,130
Don't stay up late all the time.

565
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:30,070
You're all grown up and sensible now.

566
00:21:30,070 --> 00:21:32,750
Make your own decisions
if anything happens.

567
00:21:36,830 --> 00:21:38,030
Just go back upstairs.

568
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:40,160
It's fine. I have nothing to do anyway.

569
00:21:40,350 --> 00:21:41,680
School just started with so much to do.

570
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:42,350
Hurry back

571
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:43,750
and do what you need to do.

572
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,770
Your mom doesn't know this.

573
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:49,860
Take it.

574
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,110
You've given me enough already.

575
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:52,330
We don't know
if the cafeteria food is good.

576
00:21:52,330 --> 00:21:54,170
Go buy yourself whatever you want.

577
00:21:54,170 --> 00:21:54,630
Take it.

578
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:59,350
Put that tuition money away safely.

579
00:21:59,350 --> 00:22:00,400
D-Don't lose it.

580
00:22:07,070 --> 00:22:07,640
Bye.

581
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,340
Call Dad if anything happens.

582
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,900
Call me when you get home, too.

583
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:23,720
We were able to transfer
back to Shanghai this time,

584
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:26,050
all thanks to your father's great effort.

585
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:28,510
All right.
Now that you know where we live,

586
00:22:28,710 --> 00:22:30,270
feel free to come visit us
whenever you want.

587
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:31,730
Got it. Thank you, Mr. Yan.

588
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,640
I'll definitely visit you
whenever I have time.

589
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:34,030
Good.

590
00:22:35,980 --> 00:22:37,110
Mom, let me help you.

591
00:22:37,330 --> 00:22:38,930
Don't bother. You guys chat.

592
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:41,830
Guoqing,

593
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:44,790
you are very welcome to visit our home.

594
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:47,410
Xiaodan just arrived in Shanghai,

595
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:48,960
and she doesn't have many friends here.

596
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:49,650
Please

597
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:51,370
take good care of her, okay?

598
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,530
Don't worry, ma'am.

599
00:22:52,550 --> 00:22:54,680
If she needs help in the future,

600
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,720
I'll do my best as long as it's

601
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:56,510
within my capabilities.

602
00:22:56,510 --> 00:22:57,270
Okay, great.

603
00:22:57,630 --> 00:22:59,910
Sweetie, say thank you to Guoqing.

604
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:02,080
Is it really necessary?

605
00:23:02,110 --> 00:23:04,690
Aren't my dad and his dad old classmates?

606
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,590
Senior Chen and I are classmates, too.

607
00:23:06,590 --> 00:23:08,770
We're just continuing that friendship.

608
00:23:08,770 --> 00:23:09,570
That's right.

609
00:23:09,590 --> 00:23:10,330
She's right.

610
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:12,770
Sweetie, you do have a way with words.

611
00:23:12,770 --> 00:23:15,100
Come on, help me peel some apples.

612
00:23:20,070 --> 00:23:20,680
Guoqing.

613
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,400
I have a question for you.

614
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:25,670
Do you have a girlfriend?

615
00:23:26,540 --> 00:23:28,020
I don't have a girlfriend now.

616
00:23:28,020 --> 00:23:29,120
Oh, no girlfriend?

617
00:23:30,290 --> 00:23:31,960
You're so outstanding, Guoqing.

618
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:35,160
You must pick carefully
when finding a girlfriend.

619
00:23:35,550 --> 00:23:36,680
You and Xiaodan are

620
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:38,240
in the same school.

621
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:40,050
-You can help each other.
-Alright, enough.

622
00:23:40,050 --> 00:23:40,700
Look at you.

623
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:42,940
You're embarrassing the kid.

624
00:23:43,110 --> 00:23:45,800
[Shanghai Tongzhou University]

625
00:23:43,310 --> 00:23:44,350
That's nothing.

626
00:23:46,350 --> 00:23:49,640
Back in high school,
I always dreamed of skipping class.

627
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:50,720
Now it's great.

628
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,400
I'm not used

629
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,000
to the sharp drop in classes.

630
00:23:53,030 --> 00:23:55,630
Then you can sit in on classes
at other schools.

631
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,280
Won't the teachers mind?

632
00:23:58,030 --> 00:23:59,720
We'll take classes together.

633
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:01,200
Several classes are combined,

634
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,930
and nobody knows anybody else.

635
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:05,840
Then that's a good idea.

636
00:24:06,030 --> 00:24:08,400
I'll look up classes
at the School of Arts later.

637
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:09,850
Actually, small classes are nice too.

638
00:24:09,850 --> 00:24:10,720
Because teachers

639
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:13,120
really welcome other students sitting in.

640
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:16,180
Meng Ge, long time no see!

641
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:18,360
You've grown taller again?

642
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:18,920
What?

643
00:24:20,350 --> 00:24:21,240
Let me introduce you.

644
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,550
This is my high school classmate, Meng Ge.

645
00:24:23,550 --> 00:24:25,030
This is my senior, Chen Guoqing.

646
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:25,480
Hello.

647
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:26,240
Hello.

648
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,240
Since your friend is here for you,

649
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,370
I'll leave you to it.

650
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:31,910
If you need any help at school,
just come to me.

651
00:24:31,910 --> 00:24:33,200
Okay. Thank you, Senior Chen.

652
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:34,270
I'm off. Bye-bye.

653
00:24:34,270 --> 00:24:34,880
Bye-bye.

654
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:35,760
Bye-bye, miss.

655
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:38,680
Look.

656
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:40,300
-Wait.
-Look at the library.

657
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:41,110
What's wrong?

658
00:24:41,110 --> 00:24:42,240
Is he pursuing you?

659
00:24:43,750 --> 00:24:45,400
What? No way.

660
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,550
His dad and my dad are old classmates.

661
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:49,010
They've known each other.

662
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:49,900
Really?

663
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:52,400
Can we drop it?

664
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:53,760
Let's talk about you.

665
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:55,930
Where did you get into?

666
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:56,880
Shanghai Huadong?

667
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,400
So you don't even remember.

668
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:59,400
Huadong University
of Finance and Economics.

669
00:24:59,400 --> 00:24:59,960
Right.

670
00:25:00,110 --> 00:25:01,840
Xia Lei is at Shanghai Huigong.

671
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:02,830
Your schools are so close.

672
00:25:02,830 --> 00:25:03,890
Haven't you met up?

673
00:25:04,030 --> 00:25:05,360
I didn't even know that.

674
00:25:05,550 --> 00:25:07,970
So you still care about me,

675
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:11,430
coming all this way just to see me.

676
00:25:11,450 --> 00:25:12,530
You bet.

677
00:25:12,710 --> 00:25:15,040
Alright. I'll treat you at the cafeteria.

678
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:22,680
Here we go.

679
00:25:24,150 --> 00:25:24,950
This is yours.

680
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:27,960
Honestly, I

681
00:25:28,070 --> 00:25:30,590
really wanted to treat you
to my hometown dishes.

682
00:25:30,590 --> 00:25:31,880
But what are these?

683
00:25:32,950 --> 00:25:35,280
Another day of missing Mr. Xia's cooking.

684
00:25:37,270 --> 00:25:37,870
By the way,

685
00:25:39,590 --> 00:25:41,600
why did you decide
to apply to a school in Shanghai?

686
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:43,060
I wanted to study finance.

687
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:46,740
You never mentioned that in high school.

688
00:25:47,270 --> 00:25:49,270
I thought you would
either go back to Beijing

689
00:25:49,270 --> 00:25:50,000
or go abroad.

690
00:25:50,270 --> 00:25:52,720
I didn't expect you to come to Shanghai
to study finance

691
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,070
and deal with math.

692
00:25:54,350 --> 00:25:57,030
Just hearing the word "math"
gives me a headache.

693
00:25:57,030 --> 00:25:59,350
I think interpersonal relationships
give me a bigger headache.

694
00:25:59,350 --> 00:26:00,480
Social etiquette

695
00:26:01,110 --> 00:26:03,110
always makes me feel rather bewildered.

696
00:26:03,110 --> 00:26:05,020
I think numbers are clear-cut.

697
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:06,320
Dealing with numbers is

698
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,850
actually quite rewarding.

699
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:13,270
I always knew you had a clear head,

700
00:26:13,870 --> 00:26:15,750
but I didn't expect it to be this clear.

701
00:26:15,750 --> 00:26:17,810
You've got it all figured out as well.

702
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:20,550
Back in high school,
given those recitation contests

703
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:22,480
and the hosting competitions
you participated in,

704
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:23,480
I thought you

705
00:26:23,750 --> 00:26:25,810
didn't take your studies seriously.

706
00:26:26,110 --> 00:26:29,110
But you ended up
in Tongzhou's architecture program.

707
00:26:31,510 --> 00:26:33,350
Actually, when I set my goal,

708
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:35,720
I also didn't have much confidence.

709
00:26:35,750 --> 00:26:37,830
Then, after what happened to Xiaoman,

710
00:26:37,830 --> 00:26:39,890
I studied like crazy for a few months.

711
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:43,070
My additional art test scores were
pretty good.

712
00:26:43,070 --> 00:26:45,270
Guess I had a bit of luck on my side.

713
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,170
Is Xiaoman getting released soon?

714
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,750
October 18th.

715
00:26:56,770 --> 00:26:59,650
[One month later]

716
00:26:59,240 --> 00:26:59,800
Honey.

717
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:02,790
I've prepped all the ingredients.

718
00:27:02,790 --> 00:27:04,120
I'm leaving this to you.

719
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:05,350
I have to... I've got to go now.

720
00:27:05,350 --> 00:27:06,200
Leave the soup alone.

721
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:06,590
I see.

722
00:27:06,590 --> 00:27:07,240
I'll finish it when I'm back.

723
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:08,270
I need... I need

724
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:09,440
to add the egg drop on top.

725
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:10,720
You've got everything else done?

726
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:11,980
Just the egg drop left.

727
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,000
Who is it?

728
00:27:22,550 --> 00:27:23,240
Ding?

729
00:27:24,220 --> 00:27:24,810
Yan!

730
00:27:25,270 --> 00:27:27,920
Is today the day to pick up Xiaoman?

731
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,270
Yes. I'm

732
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,720
just about to go get him.

733
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:32,920
Don't get me started.

734
00:27:33,210 --> 00:27:33,930
Xiaodan

735
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:36,400
insisted on taking a train ride
that lasts dozens of hours,

736
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,030
saying that she wanted to go back
and pick him up herself.

737
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:40,720
Her mom and I spent ages
persuading her not to.

738
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,610
Yeah, they're close.

739
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,000
Actually, I also think

740
00:27:49,350 --> 00:27:50,350
there's really no need for that.

741
00:27:50,350 --> 00:27:51,080
The reason is

742
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:55,240
that if Xiaodan and Xia Lei
do well in class in Shanghai

743
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:57,170
and focus on their studies, I guess

744
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:59,000
Xiaoman will be quite happy.

745
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:01,830
Xiaodan just got here.

746
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,070
I think it'll take her some time

747
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:06,790
to adapt to this new environment,

748
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:08,240
whether it's life

749
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:09,900
or the academic environment.

750
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:12,200
Sometimes I'm worried, too.

751
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:15,400
I'm afraid Xiaoman might distract her.

752
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,030
So what?

753
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:21,750
Your kid is a treasure,

754
00:28:21,750 --> 00:28:22,950
but is ours any worse?

755
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,440
Don't... Don't get mad.

756
00:28:24,830 --> 00:28:26,160
That's not what I meant.

757
00:28:28,030 --> 00:28:30,690
Let's analyze
the reality objectively, right?

758
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:33,270
Xiaodan has made it out, after all.

759
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:36,500
There's no way
I'll let her go back to the mountains.

760
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,400
As for what's between the two kids,

761
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:40,240
we adults are well aware of it.

762
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:43,660
Tell me yourself.
Do you think they have a future together?

763
00:28:43,850 --> 00:28:46,030
Your kid is 18 now,
even if she's unsettled!

764
00:28:46,030 --> 00:28:48,160
Let the kids solve their own problems.

765
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:52,110
What's with the shouting? What's going on?

766
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:52,590
What?

767
00:28:52,590 --> 00:28:54,920
Like our kid is shameless or something...

768
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:57,990
Who was it?

769
00:28:57,990 --> 00:29:00,390
Go out for a bit.
I have something to handle.

770
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:14,550
Zhang Xiaoman, come out with me.

771
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,400
I'm off.

772
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:23,440
Bye.

773
00:29:29,110 --> 00:29:29,790
Officer.

774
00:29:31,670 --> 00:29:32,470
Xiaoman,

775
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:34,200
after you leave,

776
00:29:34,250 --> 00:29:35,780
I won't get a taste of honey.

777
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:44,790
You keep it.

778
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:45,860
Take it.

779
00:29:46,550 --> 00:29:47,120
Really?

780
00:29:47,750 --> 00:29:48,950
Keep growing it here.

781
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:50,980
It looks quite festive

782
00:29:51,380 --> 00:29:52,860
in the room.

783
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:55,590
Remember to water it.

784
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:58,720
Don't... Don't water it too much, though.

785
00:29:58,720 --> 00:30:00,850
Overwatering will kill it instantly.

786
00:30:02,750 --> 00:30:03,440
Do you hear me?

787
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:04,240
Yeah, I got it.

788
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:05,790
Listen, if you kill it,

789
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:07,500
I'll deal with you.

790
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:08,850
Are you coming back?

791
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:11,620
Won't you get out eventually?

792
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:13,370
You're in your teens.

793
00:30:13,370 --> 00:30:15,430
Don't cause trouble when you get out.

794
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:16,400
Don't worry.

795
00:30:17,030 --> 00:30:18,100
Let's go, Zhang Xiaoman.

796
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:18,580
Okay.

797
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,170
I'm leaving.

798
00:30:20,550 --> 00:30:21,550
Behave yourself.

799
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:24,300
Alright, I'm taking my leave.

800
00:30:25,110 --> 00:30:26,510
Get out. Don't look back.

801
00:30:27,540 --> 00:30:28,400
Thank you, Officer.

802
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:28,830
Okay.

803
00:30:31,900 --> 00:30:32,500
Off you go.

804
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:34,780
Thank you.

805
00:30:43,830 --> 00:30:44,590
Mr. Ding.

806
00:30:49,550 --> 00:30:50,400
I was planning

807
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,600
to use some mugwort
to sweep away your bad luck.

808
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:56,640
But my wife said juvenile detention

809
00:30:56,900 --> 00:30:58,360
doesn't count as jailing,

810
00:30:58,440 --> 00:30:59,370
so let's skip it.

811
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,090
You've lost weight.

812
00:31:06,750 --> 00:31:07,810
Being thin is fine.

813
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:09,930
You've grown taller again.

814
00:31:10,750 --> 00:31:12,550
Come on, let's go. Get in the car.

815
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:13,640
Let's go home.

816
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:14,920
I'll get you cleaned up first.

817
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:15,890
You have a car now?

818
00:31:15,890 --> 00:31:16,610
Let's go.

819
00:31:18,790 --> 00:31:19,390
Excuse me.

820
00:31:19,730 --> 00:31:20,620
Sorry to trouble you, sir.

821
00:31:20,620 --> 00:31:21,750
Please take us back.

822
00:31:21,890 --> 00:31:22,490
Thank you.

823
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:24,240
Come on.

824
00:31:27,150 --> 00:31:27,830
Get in.

825
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,100
Watch your leg.

826
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:31,400
You sit in the front?

827
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:31,990
Yeah.

828
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:46,500
Xiaoman is back.

829
00:31:46,750 --> 00:31:47,240
Yeah, he's back.

830
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:47,680
Okay.

831
00:31:51,150 --> 00:31:51,920
Why are you following behind me?

832
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:52,780
Are you my tail?

833
00:31:53,490 --> 00:31:54,350
You are educated.

834
00:31:54,350 --> 00:31:55,720
You aren't... You are good people.

835
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:56,400
Hold your head up.

836
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:57,460
Walk in front of me.

837
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:04,920
Mr. Ding!

838
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,350
Xiaoman!

839
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:07,130
You're back.

840
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:07,640
Yeah.

841
00:32:08,090 --> 00:32:09,420
Father and son are here.

842
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:10,240
Your ticket.

843
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:10,920
Give us one key.

844
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:11,550
I'm not bathing.

845
00:32:11,550 --> 00:32:12,160
Take it.

846
00:32:12,890 --> 00:32:13,450
Go ahead.

847
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:14,790
Say hello. This is...

848
00:32:14,790 --> 00:32:15,920
Mr. Li and Mr. Zhang.

849
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:16,970
Mr. Li, Mr. Zhang.

850
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:18,750
The water is great today.

851
00:32:18,750 --> 00:32:19,660
Go in and wash up.

852
00:32:19,660 --> 00:32:20,080
Go ahead.

853
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:20,970
He's a good kid.

854
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:21,400
Go on.

855
00:32:21,420 --> 00:32:22,420
-Good boy.
-Go in.

856
00:32:25,590 --> 00:32:26,250
Washing up?

857
00:32:26,310 --> 00:32:26,840
Mr. Ding.

858
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:27,920
What number? 4.

859
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:29,030
Four is here, this way.

860
00:32:29,030 --> 00:32:29,590
Don't just talk.

861
00:32:29,590 --> 00:32:31,200
When have you ever treated me to a drink?

862
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,110
I promise I'll treat you this time.

863
00:32:32,110 --> 00:32:33,370
Do something for real.

864
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:36,820
Gosh, I dropped it.

865
00:32:37,310 --> 00:32:38,170
Here is the soap

866
00:32:38,170 --> 00:32:39,100
and the shampoo.

867
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:41,760
Take them off.

868
00:32:42,550 --> 00:32:44,240
Take the clothes off and throw them away.

869
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:45,300
Let's start fresh.

870
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:46,900
I brought you a new set.

871
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:00,890
Put on the slippers.

872
00:33:00,890 --> 00:33:01,350
Come on.

873
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:03,780
Take off

874
00:33:03,790 --> 00:33:05,390
a-and throw away your socks.

875
00:33:05,790 --> 00:33:06,650
Give them to me.

876
00:33:06,930 --> 00:33:08,140
Throw away the socks, too?

877
00:33:08,140 --> 00:33:09,240
Why would you keep them?

878
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:10,970
No need. T-Throw them all away.

879
00:33:13,990 --> 00:33:14,920
We have new ones.

880
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,070
Go ahead.

881
00:33:16,090 --> 00:33:17,240
Take this basket with you.

882
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:19,000
Change into this when you come out.

883
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,400
C-Change into this later!

884
00:33:20,400 --> 00:33:22,300
Oh, my...
Have you never taken a shower before?

885
00:33:22,300 --> 00:33:22,830
Go.

886
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:27,240
Get in! I'll wait for you.

887
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,370
I'm not washing. Go.

888
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:30,500
Clean yourself up!

889
00:33:57,170 --> 00:33:57,960
Mr. Ding.

890
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,820
I'm g-going to my grandma's place
to take a look.

891
00:34:06,620 --> 00:34:07,420
As you should.

892
00:34:07,550 --> 00:34:09,020
Go ahead. I'll wait for you.

893
00:34:09,020 --> 00:34:10,090
Are you staying here?

894
00:34:10,090 --> 00:34:11,000
You go ahead.

895
00:34:38,630 --> 00:34:39,710
Where are the bowls and chopsticks?
Hurry up.

896
00:34:39,710 --> 00:34:40,630
Coming.

897
00:34:43,239 --> 00:34:43,989
Here you are.

898
00:34:44,830 --> 00:34:45,690
Enjoy the food.

899
00:34:47,639 --> 00:34:48,770
You've lost weight.

900
00:34:49,630 --> 00:34:50,360
Haven't you?

901
00:34:50,550 --> 00:34:51,840
The kid's lost weight.

902
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:53,670
But he looks energetic.

903
00:34:55,030 --> 00:34:55,760
That's good.

904
00:34:56,030 --> 00:34:56,550
Eat up.

905
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:59,020
Ding made these meat dishes just for you.

906
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:01,550
Eat whatever you like. Have plenty.

907
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:02,630
Um...

908
00:35:03,030 --> 00:35:04,630
Mr. Ding, Mrs. Ding.

909
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:10,840
I've caused trouble for everyone
because of this case.

910
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:11,670
I'm sorry.

911
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:13,610
What is this kid talking about?

912
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:14,970
What did I just tell you?

913
00:35:14,970 --> 00:35:16,150
Don't be afraid of falling.

914
00:35:16,150 --> 00:35:17,800
Get back up, and you're still a man.

915
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:18,550
Exactly.

916
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,030
It wasn't a huge mistake.

917
00:35:20,030 --> 00:35:21,760
What? Well, you're also wrong about it.

918
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:22,760
How am I wrong?

919
00:35:22,780 --> 00:35:24,040
A mistake is a mistake.

920
00:35:24,190 --> 00:35:25,730
The part that wasn't wrong is separate.

921
00:35:25,730 --> 00:35:26,550
You have to tell them apart.

922
00:35:26,550 --> 00:35:28,010
His intentions were good.

923
00:35:28,170 --> 00:35:29,830
Yes, right. Good intentions.

924
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:32,590
You were doing it
for our plant's safety, weren't you?

925
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:34,450
Your heart was in the right place.

926
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:36,000
Come on, eat up.

927
00:35:36,110 --> 00:35:37,110
Dig in.

928
00:35:37,540 --> 00:35:39,140
Eat to your heart's content.

929
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,540
I just remembered something.

930
00:35:41,590 --> 00:35:42,710
On my way back,

931
00:35:42,710 --> 00:35:44,150
I ran into Xia Lei's mother.

932
00:35:44,150 --> 00:35:45,030
She said

933
00:35:45,230 --> 00:35:47,490
Xia Lei and Xiaodan are going to call you.

934
00:35:48,230 --> 00:35:48,960
When?

935
00:35:49,590 --> 00:35:50,850
She said after dinner.

936
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:51,790
Around 8.

937
00:35:52,780 --> 00:35:53,910
Let's eat. Hurry up.

938
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:56,420
I'll wait here then. Perfect timing.

939
00:35:56,980 --> 00:35:57,790
Just wait.

940
00:35:58,880 --> 00:35:59,630
Eat more.

941
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,100
Look at him.

942
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,440
He got so happy

943
00:36:02,460 --> 00:36:04,320
as soon as he heard about the call.

944
00:36:04,490 --> 00:36:04,970
Happy?

945
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:06,840
How can you tell that he's happy?

946
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,480
You're always talking nonsense.

947
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:09,340
Isn't he happy?

948
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:10,030
He looks happy to me.

949
00:36:10,030 --> 00:36:10,830
Are you happy?

950
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:11,960
Even I'm happy.

951
00:36:12,760 --> 00:36:14,160
Do... Do you want a drink?

952
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:15,670
Come on, hurry up!

953
00:36:15,670 --> 00:36:16,630
It's almost 8:30.

954
00:36:16,630 --> 00:36:17,760
Where have you been?

955
00:36:18,610 --> 00:36:19,940
Class ran late tonight.

956
00:36:20,310 --> 00:36:21,910
The teacher didn't let us go.

957
00:36:22,590 --> 00:36:24,390
Wait, how many cards do you have?

958
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:26,000
Let me see.

959
00:36:26,220 --> 00:36:27,260
I have two of 30.

960
00:36:27,590 --> 00:36:29,480
There's 20 yuan left on this card.

961
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:31,590
I only called home once this month,

962
00:36:31,590 --> 00:36:32,990
just to save it for today.

963
00:36:33,670 --> 00:36:34,670
Brilliant. Look.

964
00:36:34,670 --> 00:36:37,230
I haven't used this one of 50
and these two of 30.

965
00:36:37,230 --> 00:36:38,420
We can talk all night.

966
00:36:38,420 --> 00:36:39,010
Good.

967
00:36:39,110 --> 00:36:39,800
Perfect.

968
00:36:40,030 --> 00:36:40,880
Hurry.

969
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:43,800
Well, call Mr. Ding.

970
00:36:44,030 --> 00:36:46,360
My mom said
they're all at his place today.

971
00:36:46,710 --> 00:36:47,390
Okay.

972
00:37:03,230 --> 00:37:04,360
It can't go through.

973
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:05,880
Why?

974
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:07,110
Let me try.

975
00:37:08,630 --> 00:37:10,290
Is the phone malfunctioning?

976
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,800
Why does it have to malfunction now?

977
00:37:15,230 --> 00:37:16,880
Do you remember those comrades of mine?

978
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:17,480
I do.

979
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:19,360
Those same few guys.

980
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,590
Gu Yonghua.

981
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:22,160
Cao Li.

982
00:37:22,190 --> 00:37:22,720
Ma Leizi.

983
00:37:22,750 --> 00:37:23,280
Ma Leizi.

984
00:37:28,150 --> 00:37:29,550
It's really not working.

985
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,010
It won't go through?

986
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:34,760
What should we do then?

987
00:37:38,230 --> 00:37:39,760
Well, can you believe that?

988
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:41,480
Getting married is

989
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:43,030
a serious matter.

990
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:44,710
What's going on?

991
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:47,450
What's the date today?

992
00:37:47,450 --> 00:37:49,230
Xiaoman was supposed to be released today.

993
00:37:49,230 --> 00:37:51,230
Yeah. Then why aren't they
answering the phone?

994
00:37:51,230 --> 00:37:52,670
Well, I mean, you shouldn't

995
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:54,330
take feelings too seriously.

996
00:37:54,670 --> 00:37:55,910
How can you not take them seriously?

997
00:37:55,910 --> 00:37:56,670
Xiaoman, Xiaoman.

998
00:37:56,670 --> 00:37:57,930
Do you think I'm right?

999
00:37:58,800 --> 00:37:59,220
You're right.

1000
00:37:59,220 --> 00:38:00,230
-Right about what?
-Yes.

1001
00:38:00,230 --> 00:38:01,760
People need to be faithful, don't they?

1002
00:38:01,760 --> 00:38:02,880
Is Master Ding right?

1003
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:03,480
Master Ding is wrong.

1004
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,000
See?

1005
00:38:04,670 --> 00:38:05,550
One minute you say I'm right,

1006
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:06,480
the next you say I'm wrong.

1007
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:07,360
Are you even listening?

1008
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,420
Are you listening?

1009
00:38:09,530 --> 00:38:11,060
What are you talking about?

1010
00:38:11,590 --> 00:38:12,440
I know, boy.

1011
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:13,800
He's spacing out.

1012
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:15,250
Y-You're waiting
for their call, aren't you?

1013
00:38:15,250 --> 00:38:16,560
Well, w-weren't they
supposed to call at 8?

1014
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:17,000
Yes.

1015
00:38:17,020 --> 00:38:18,230
It's already 8... 8:30 now.

1016
00:38:18,230 --> 00:38:18,830
It's fine.

1017
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:20,510
Maybe they're having

1018
00:38:21,590 --> 00:38:22,450
extra classes.

1019
00:38:22,820 --> 00:38:24,490
Just like Mr. Ding working overtime.

1020
00:38:24,490 --> 00:38:26,440
Stop blabbering. Cut it out... I...

1021
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:27,480
I go to work to earn money.

1022
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:28,440
Do they make money at school?

1023
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,480
It's not the case of working overtime.

1024
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:30,150
Well, they love studying.

1025
00:38:30,150 --> 00:38:31,000
Cut it out if you don't get it.

1026
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,750
So how do you know
the class didn't run late?

1027
00:38:32,750 --> 00:38:34,880
There's a time difference
between Shanghai and here.

1028
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:35,480
That's it.

1029
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:36,340
Really?

1030
00:38:36,950 --> 00:38:37,880
-I need to use the bathroom.
-There's time difference?

1031
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:39,670
We are thousands of miles apart.

1032
00:38:39,670 --> 00:38:40,670
Maybe he's right.

1033
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,790
Maybe there's a time difference,

1034
00:38:42,790 --> 00:38:44,190
like half an hour or what.

1035
00:38:44,670 --> 00:38:45,800
Just wait a bit longer.

1036
00:38:45,800 --> 00:38:46,860
Drink some of this.

1037
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:48,480
And eat Mr. Ding's pancake.

1038
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:49,930
Is the phone s-still in the inner room?

1039
00:38:49,930 --> 00:38:50,410
Yeah.

1040
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:52,000
I... I'll call Xia Lei.

1041
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,000
Go ahead and call.

1042
00:38:53,040 --> 00:38:54,230
It's right by the bed.

1043
00:38:54,230 --> 00:38:55,160
Call and ask him.

1044
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,570
Why didn't you call?

1045
00:39:19,670 --> 00:39:21,070
I'm going for a walk with Mr. Ding.

1046
00:39:21,070 --> 00:39:22,170
I'll go down and check.

1047
00:39:22,170 --> 00:39:23,510
-He's been gone for a while.
-Is it cold outside?

1048
00:39:23,510 --> 00:39:24,310
No. It's fine.

1049
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:32,360
Xiaoman.

1050
00:39:33,710 --> 00:39:34,990
I have a question for you.

1051
00:39:34,990 --> 00:39:36,520
You're 18 this year, right?

1052
00:39:37,110 --> 00:39:38,230
Technically speaking,

1053
00:39:38,230 --> 00:39:40,230
you can drink now. Have some.

1054
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:43,970
Mr. Ding, why did you unplug the phone?

1055
00:39:47,070 --> 00:39:48,590
What... What?

1056
00:39:49,590 --> 00:39:50,320
I don't know.

1057
00:39:50,610 --> 00:39:51,470
What happened?

1058
00:39:55,070 --> 00:39:56,070
Mr. Ding, I know.

1059
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:59,070
y-you must've done this for my own good.

1060
00:39:59,070 --> 00:40:00,710
But I want

1061
00:40:00,710 --> 00:40:01,510
to know why.

1062
00:40:12,880 --> 00:40:14,940
Boy, I won't keep it from you anymore.

1063
00:40:16,870 --> 00:40:18,100
I scolded Yan today.

1064
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:19,800
What did he do?

1065
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:21,070
Why did you scold him?

1066
00:40:21,070 --> 00:40:22,150
What e-else

1067
00:40:22,150 --> 00:40:23,230
does he need to do

1068
00:40:23,230 --> 00:40:24,290
for me to scold him?

1069
00:40:24,670 --> 00:40:25,930
Only a child needs coaxing.

1070
00:40:25,930 --> 00:40:28,000
I just scolded him casually. So what?

1071
00:40:32,150 --> 00:40:34,630
Like you're throwing yourself at him!

1072
00:40:34,650 --> 00:40:36,590
Are we so thick-skinned?

1073
00:40:46,450 --> 00:40:47,220
Mr. Ding.

1074
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:49,280
Well,

1075
00:40:51,590 --> 00:40:52,670
Xiaodan

1076
00:40:53,280 --> 00:40:55,940
and the others
all went to Shanghai for college.

1077
00:40:57,070 --> 00:40:59,330
Do they think I'm not good enough for her?

1078
00:41:01,990 --> 00:41:03,030
You wimp.

1079
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,250
Truly hopeless.

1080
00:41:06,010 --> 00:41:07,000
Look at yourself.

1081
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:07,880
Go look in the mirror anytime.

1082
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:08,320
Look at you.

1083
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:09,510
W-With this height,

1084
00:41:09,710 --> 00:41:11,000
standing here like a solid rock,

1085
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:12,600
and your looks, you still...

1086
00:41:20,190 --> 00:41:22,070
No matter how things go

1087
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:24,710
between you and Xiaodan...

1088
00:41:24,710 --> 00:41:25,710
I-I don't know...

1089
00:41:25,710 --> 00:41:27,110
But I-I don't care.

1090
00:41:28,190 --> 00:41:29,190
But in my heart,

1091
00:41:31,270 --> 00:41:32,200
you are the best.

1092
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:33,840
No one beats you.

1093
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,110
Bar none.

1094
00:41:36,580 --> 00:41:37,180
Top notch.

1095
00:41:38,120 --> 00:41:39,180
Do you understand?

1096
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:43,720
If you do, let's go drink.

1097
00:41:43,830 --> 00:41:44,360
Let's go.

1098
00:41:44,410 --> 00:41:45,480
Let's go home.

1099
00:41:46,070 --> 00:41:46,980
Why are you holding me?

1100
00:41:46,980 --> 00:41:48,170
I'm... I'm fine.

1101
00:41:48,510 --> 00:41:49,040
Let's go.

1102
00:41:49,630 --> 00:41:50,760
Let's go for a drink.

1103
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:53,000
You're an 18-year-old man now...

1104
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,410
It's no big deal.

1105
00:41:58,510 --> 00:41:59,170
Be careful.

1106
00:41:59,290 --> 00:42:00,290
You mind the step.

1107
00:42:00,470 --> 00:42:00,880
He...

1108
00:42:01,910 --> 00:42:03,450
Did anything happen to him?

1109
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:06,230
Could something have happened again?

1110
00:42:06,230 --> 00:42:07,630
So he was not released today?

1111
00:42:07,630 --> 00:42:08,430
No, no way.

1112
00:42:10,230 --> 00:42:11,090
How about this?

1113
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:12,840
I'll call home tomorrow.

1114
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:14,070
I'll ask them

1115
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,890
to bring Xiaoman to my place on Sunday.

1116
00:42:17,040 --> 00:42:17,800
We can call again then.

1117
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:20,070
Okay. He should be fine, right?

1118
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:21,960
Don't worry.

1119
00:42:23,730 --> 00:42:26,390
There's something
called probability theory.

1120
00:42:26,670 --> 00:42:27,400
For example,

1121
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:30,070
we encounter certain things in a day.

1122
00:42:30,380 --> 00:42:31,180
Like what?

1123
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:33,480
One person

1124
00:42:34,030 --> 00:42:34,920
might meet

1125
00:42:35,070 --> 00:42:37,280
another person twice in a day.

1126
00:42:37,960 --> 00:42:39,400
These are all low-probability events,

1127
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:40,710
so you don't need to worry.

1128
00:42:40,710 --> 00:42:41,710
Alright.

1129
00:42:43,190 --> 00:42:44,440
I thought I could

1130
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:46,070
hear Xiaoman's voice today.

1131
00:42:49,320 --> 00:42:50,650
Go back and hit the sack.

1132
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:53,580
You go back early, too.

1133
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,530
Keep yours. Don't lose them.

1134
00:42:59,530 --> 00:43:00,260
Of course.

1135
00:43:00,710 --> 00:43:02,440
Let's call him next time. I'm off.

1136
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:03,100
Goodnight.

1137
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:03,840
Goodnight.
